      "message": "\u003e And another thing: glibc ld.so looks like it’ll break if you try to feed it a module where the PT_LOAD entries, in sequence, don’t refer to increasing load addresses, or at least where the first and last PT_LOADs don’t refer to the first and last mapped segments in address order. (_dl_map_object_from_fd from elf/dl-load.c, handling of maxlength). Bionic looks like it might support it, though.\n\nThe kernel does the same thing as glibc. fs/binfmt_elf.c total_mapping_size().",
